The paper proposes a framework that combines deep clustering and recurrent neural networks for short-term road traffic prediction. The use of deep clustering suggests a focus on unsupervised learning, which is commonly associated with the machine learning subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also utilizes convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which falls under the computer vision subfield (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) suggests a focus on sequential data analysis, which is commonly associated with the artificial intelligence subfield (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a model sharing strategy, which may fall under the neural networks and learning subfield (cs.NE) or the systems and control subfield (cs.SI). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, with cs.NE and cs.SI being less likely but still possible.
